
@startuml

' Define classes
class Faculty {
    - name: String
    - numberOfInstitutes: int
    - dean: Employee
}

class Institute {
    - name: String
    - address: String
    - faculty: Faculty
}

class Employee {
    - socialSecurityNumber: String
    - name: String
    - email: String
    + type: String  ' "Research" or "Administrative"
}

class ResearchAssistant {
    - fieldOfResearch: String
    - projects: List<Project>
    - institutes: List<Institute>
    -- extends Employee
}

class Lecturer {
    - courses: List<Course>
    -- extends ResearchAssistant
}

class Project {
    - name: String
    - startDate: Date
    - endDate: Date
    - hours: int
    - researchAssistant: ResearchAssistant
}

class Course {
    - courseID: String
    - name: String
    - weeklyDuration: int
    - lecturer: Lecturer
}

' Relationships
Faculty "1" -- "0..*" Institute : consists of
Institute "1" -- "1" Faculty : belongs to
Employee "1" -- "1" Faculty : dean
Employee "1" -- "0..*" ResearchAssistant : is a
ResearchAssistant "1" -- "0..*" Institute : assigned to
ResearchAssistant "1" -- "0..*" Project : involved in
Project "1" -- "1" ResearchAssistant : has
ResearchAssistant "1" -- "0..*" Lecturer : is a
Lecturer "1" -- "0..*" Course : teaches
Course "1" -- "1" Lecturer : has

@enduml

### Explanation:
- **Faculty** contains multiple **Institutes**, and each **Institute** belongs to one **Faculty**.
- A **Faculty** has one **Dean**, who is an **Employee**.
- **Employees** are either **Research Assistants** or **Administrative Staff**.
- **Research Assistants** can be assigned to one or more **Institutes**, and may be involved in **Projects**.
- **Lecturers** are a subclass of **Research Assistants** and teach **Courses**.
- **Courses** have a unique **courseID**, a **name**, and a **weekly duration**.

